{
  "texts": [
    "Implementation Details (Supplementary) Coordinate NormalizationTo ensure consistent spatial representation across images of varying sizes, all bounding box coordinates are normalized.",
    "The bottom-left corner of the image is defined as the origin, and coordinates are expressed in relative terms with respect to image dimensions.",
    "Specifically, each candidate region is formatted as:(center x, center y, width, height)where center x and center y are the center coordinates of the bounding box, and width, height denote the box dimensions.",
    "All values are normalized to fall within [0, 1] and rounded to three decimal places.",
    "This format is designed to improve parsing and interpretability by large language models (LLMs and MLLMs) during reasoning."
  ]
}